{"tid":770164,"cid":6,"subCid":0,"title":"上季被誤判最多受害者竟係利物浦；誤判最大得益者竟係曼聯","createTime":"2018-08-07T00:06:51.000Z","updateTime":"2018-08-27T23:52:33.000Z","uid":5191,"like":32,"dislike":6,"uniUserReply":53,"replies":[{"pid":"7d77840432012da8fc90bd5a7fb594d85a284ab7","tid":770164,"uid":5191,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-07T00:06:51.000Z","msg":"Liverpool unluckiest Premier League team &amp; Manchester United luckiest, says study<br />\n<br />\n56 minutes ago From the sectionPremier League  59<br />\n<br />\n Liverpool v Manchester United - Philippe Coutinho is fouled in the box<br />\n<br />\nThe study found Liverpool's 0-0 draw at home to Manchester United in October would have become a 1-0 win had the Reds been awarded a penalty<br />\nLiverpool were the 'unluckiest' team in the Premier League last season while Manchester United were the 'luckiest', new research claims.<br />\n<br />\nThe Reds dropped 12 points in matches affected by wrongly disallowed goals or incorrect decisions on penalties and red cards, says a study conducted by ESPN, Intel and the University of Bath.<br />\n<br />\nIt says United gained six points over incidents that went in their favour.<br />\n<br />\nManchester City remain top in a new simulated table accounting for 'luck'.<br />\n<br />\nHowever, the study found Huddersfield should have been relegated instead of Stoke when 'incorrect' refereeing decisions were taken into account.<br />\n<br />\nIt also found Brighton would have finished six places higher - moving up to ninth and earning an extra &pound;11.5m in prize money on their return to the top flight.<br />\n<br />\nConversely, Leicester would have finished 14th instead of ninth, ending the season with &pound;9.7m less in prize money.<br />\n<br />\nFourth-placed Liverpool would have swapped with second-placed United, and champions City fallen three points short of their 100 mark.<br />\n<br />\nHow did the 'Luck Index' work?<br />\n<br />\nA research team collaborated with ex-Premier League referee Peter Walton, analysing footage from every game of the 2017-18 Premier League season and watching for:<br />\n<br />\nGoals that should have been disallowed<br />\nIncorrectly disallowed goals<br />\nIncorrectly awarded penalties (that were scored)<br />\nPenalties that were not awarded but should have been<br />\nIncorrect red-card decisions<br />\nRed-card incidents that were missed<br />\nGoals scored after injury time overran<br />\nDeflected goals<br />\nOnce incidents had been indentified, an alternative outcome of the affected matches was predicted, using a model that also considered factors including team strength, form, and home advantage.<br />\n<br />\nFor example: in Liverpool's 0-0 draw with Manchester United at Anfield on 14 October, the study concluded Jurgen Klopp's side should have been awarded a penalty in the 63rd minute, and the new simulated scoreline was a 1-0 victory for the home side.<br />\n<br />\nOnce the process was completed, the Premier League table was redrawn to reflect the new simulated results."},{"pid":"b72e0d16db5d149a0c99a0fc10d3e9a57139a99a","tid":770164,"uid":5191,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-07T00:07:08.000Z","msg":"The research team analysed over 150 incidents and also found:<br />\n<br />\nLeicester scored three goals after injury time overran - more than any other side.<br />\nHuddersfield's John Smith's Stadium saw the most deflected goals - five. Two of those worked in the Terriers' favour.<br />\nMatt Ritchie was the 'luckiest player'. The Newcastle winger avoided two red cards, while a handball in the box against Leicester went unnoticed.<br />\nAssistant Professor Thomas Curran from the University of Bath said each game was simulated &quot;thousands of times to model how it should have turned out&quot;.<br />\n<br />\nHe said the project was &quot;one of the most detailed pieces of research we have ever conducted&quot;.<br />\n<br />\nFormer referee Walton added: &quot;The results<br />\ndemonstrate the impact and importance of refereeing decisions on a game.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;With the Premier League deciding not to introduce VAR for the coming season, it is interesting to see how much luck plays a part in the way the league unfolds.&quot;"},{"pid":"1989a95ed6cdb5815a12e7fb18dac28715c82f9f","tid":770164,"uid":16376,"like":45,"dislike":13,"score":32,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-07T00:08:15.000Z","msg":"恕婦利"},{"pid":"608a94b126cbe3208a97d18103f5abb95ec95fda","tid":770164,"uid":5191,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-07T00:08:22.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"http://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45087444\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fsport%2Ffootball%2F45087444&d=8pQux4UZmuDDUh%2BBBDQEejPUa9iY%2BpOmOVTB4fMSqaQ%3D&h=db38dd92\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fsport%2Ffootball%2F45087444&h=b31a9542\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">http://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45087444</a>"},{"pid":"6c2fd805d167358c7685c47d2b94143aae231919","tid":770164,"uid":67225,"like":3,"dislike":2,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"1989a95ed6cdb5815a12e7fb18dac28715c82f9f","tid":770164,"uid":16376,"like":45,"dislike":13,"score":32,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-07T00:08:15.000Z","msg":"恕婦利"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-07T00:09:36.000Z","msg":"出現了"},{"pid":"fa1745d06ffe4312447b2fbde9cdf2b4a09908a4","tid":770164,"uid":36236,"like":32,"dislike":26,"score":6,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-08-07T00:11:20.000Z","msg":"猁狗由歐聯怨到依家，怨婦猁"},{"pid":"1f98a4f3369c51b121a5a5dc7cbe444eaaca6654","tid":770164,"uid":5191,"like":3,"dislike":3,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"fa1745d06ffe4312447b2fbde9cdf2b4a09908a4","tid":770164,"uid":36236,"like":32,"dislike":26,"score":6,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-08-07T00:11:20.000Z","msg":"猁狗由歐聯怨到依家，怨婦猁"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-07T00:11:41.000Z","msg":"出現了"},{"pid":"9af030ad63694af5d13a5ad3b3ced9726a63edbd